      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the gold standard test for suprascapular neuropathy?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "EMG and nerve conduction velocity (NCV) studies remain the gold standard for confirming the diagnosis and localizing the exact site of nerve lesion. MRI is used to identify space-occupying lesions like ganglion cysts and to assess muscle edema and fatty infiltration."
      }
    }
  ]
};
