  <section id="faq" class="bg-white py-10 border-t border-slate-200 scroll-mt-6">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <details class="group bg-slate-50 rounded-lg cursor-pointer open:bg-emerald-50 open:ring-1 open:ring-emerald-200 transition-all">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-4 font-bold text-slate-800 text-sm list-none select-none">
            <span>What causes suprascapular neuropathy?</span>
            <span class="transition-transform group-open:rotate-180 text-slate-400 shrink-0 ml-2">
              <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Compression or traction of the nerve, most commonly from ganglion cysts, repetitive overhead activities, massive rotator cuff tears, or anatomical variations<RefLink id="1" text="Etiology" url={references[0].url} />.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-slate-50 rounded-lg cursor-pointer open:bg-emerald-50 open:ring-1 open:ring-emerald-200 transition-all">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-4 font-bold text-slate-800 text-sm list-none select-none">
            <span>How is it diagnosed?</span>
            <span class="transition-transform group-open:rotate-180 text-slate-400 shrink-0 ml-2">
              <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            EMG/NCV studies are the gold standard for confirming diagnosis. MRI identifies structural causes like cysts and assesses muscle involvement<RefLink id="3" text="Diagnosis" url={references[2].url} />.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-slate-50 rounded-lg cursor-pointer open:bg-emerald-50 open:ring-1 open:ring-emerald-200 transition-all">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-4 font-bold text-slate-800 text-sm list-none select-none">
            <span>When is surgery needed?</span>
            <span class="transition-transform group-open:rotate-180 text-slate-400 shrink-0 ml-2">
              <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Surgery is indicated for space-occupying lesions (cysts), severe atrophy, or failure of 6 months of conservative treatment<RefLink id="6" text="Surgical indications" url={references[5].url} />.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-slate-50 rounded-lg cursor-pointer open:bg-emerald-50 open:ring-1 open:ring-emerald-200 transition-all">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-4 font-bold text-slate-800 text-sm list-none select-none">
            <span>Will my muscle recover?</span>
            <span class="transition-transform group-open:rotate-180 text-slate-400 shrink-0 ml-2">
              <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            While 92-98% regain normal function, only ~50% show complete muscle volume recovery. However, this usually doesn't affect daily function or sports performance<RefLink id="12" text="Outcomes" url={references[11].url} />.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-slate-50 rounded-lg cursor-pointer open:bg-emerald-50 open:ring-1 open:ring-emerald-200 transition-all md:col-span-2 lg:col-span-2">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-4 font-bold text-slate-800 text-sm list-none select-none">
            <span>How long until I can return to sports?</span>
            <span class="transition-transform group-open:rotate-180 text-slate-400 shrink-0 ml-2">
              <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Most athletes return to competition within 3-8 months after surgery. With conservative treatment for dynamic compression, return can occur within 3 months. 92-98% return to sport, with 88-96% reaching their previous performance level<RefLink id="12" text="RTS rates" url={references[11].url} /><RefLink id="7" text="Athlete outcomes" url={references[6].url} />.
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

